    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and<strong> ground cumin</strong> to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Mix it all up, then add your<strong> free range chicken breast portion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and turn until well coated</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until browned</p>",
